flights planning. Poor at criticism may affect crew feedback.\n\nCandidate B: conscientious, stress handling, weather assessment, computer skills, but grumpy and uncooperative. Uncooperative could affect crew cooperation.\n\nCandidate C: reliable, quick correct decisions, positive crew atmosphere, but communication difficulty, egocentric, not willing to further education. Communication is crucial for long flights; egocentric may affect teamwork.\n\nCandidate D: responsibility, problem solving, concentration, adequate response to unexpected events, but arrogant, weak leadership. Leadership is important for crew.\n\nWe need provisional preference. Which candidate balances strengths and weaknesses best? Candidate C is 100% reliable and creates positive atmosphere, but communication difficulty is a serious weakness for long flights. Candidate B handles stress and weather, but uncooperative may be problematic. Candidate A has strong technical and anticipation but organizational issues could be critical for long flights planning. Candidate D has strong problem solving and responsibility but weak leadership and arrogance.\n\nProbably Candidate B might be best? He is conscientious, handles stress, good weather assessment (critical for long flights), computer skills (navigation). Weaknesses: grumpy, uncooperative, but maybe manageable. Candidate C's communication difficulty is more severe. Candidate A's unorganized could be fatal. Candidate D's weak leadership also problematic.\n\nThus provisional preference: Candidate B.\n\nWe should note uncertainties: lack of info on B's teamwork beyond uncooperative, unknown how severe. Also unknown about A's organizational severity. Ask others for more info on B's teamwork/communication, and D's leadership strengths.\n\nNow produce output."}
